Android Quick Share file sharing for Raspberry Pi OS ARM64.
RQuickShare Pi lets a Raspberry Pi send and receive files with Android Quick Share devices on the local network.
It runs as a desktop app with a tray icon, optional start-on-boot behavior, and Pi-focused Bluetooth/mDNS handling.
This is an alpha release for Raspberry Pi OS 64-bit on ARM64.

To run: Menu -> Accessories -> RQuickShare Pi
To run in a terminal: rquickshare-pi

Tip for Samsung phones: if the Pi does not appear, disable "Share with Apple devices" in Samsung Quick Share settings and try again.
